         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:argr">
 	<!--translation encoded as per EG §9.2 -->
	<p>Hail! In the elapsed Śaka year 1338, such was the time that His Majesty of Talonan took over in
	    turn (hanimbal) the piece of land (varukira) of the Lord at Paguhan, who was released in the
	    highest abode (saṅ lina riṁ pramalaya). [It] was received (kataṅgap) by the One whose task is
	    to Speak (de nira saṅ aṅucap gave) at the (stone) building Didiwa, by the patiḥ səmut (litt.
	    master Ant), by the arya pagəḥ (the Venerable Pagəh), by the arya Guna (the Venerable Guna), by
	    the patiḥ at Paguhan (by the master at Paguhan), by the patiḥ Sər̥g, by the patiḥ at Tembeṁ,
	    those are the people who received money. The amount of money [is]: 200.000, two hundred
	    thousand, two hundred thousand in total (gənəp), on Kliwon ([padu-]kaliwon), the thirteenth [day] of the waxing fortnight, the month of Asuji, signed by (litt. “bearing the name”) Sakawasa</p>
         </div>
